Nigerians have voiced their opinion about the decision of the National Youth Service Corps, Ebonyi State chapter, to de-kit two female corps members who had refused to wear the official pairs of white shorts and khaki trousers. The two youth corps members — Okafor Love Obianuju, with call-up number EB/19C/0523; and Odji Oritsetsolaye, with call-up number EB/19C/0530 — were ordered out of the camp after the disciplinary panel had found them guilty. SEE ALSO: Ebonyi NYSC sacks two female corps members for refusing to wear shorts, trousers Nigerians have since taken to the social media to express their views on the matter. See some of the reactions:       